message.content:
Analysis of Main Target Image
--------------------------------
• There are two separate “towers.”  

Left Tower (total of 7 blocks, stacked in 6 layers):  
1) Bottom layer: a flat yellow rectangular block.  
2) Above it: one large red block with a circular hole in its face.  
3) Next: another flat yellow rectangular block forming a “platform.”  
4) Two upright orange cylinders (side‐by‐side) on that platform.  
5) A third flat yellow block spanning across the tops of those cylinders.  
6) At the very top: an orange triangular wedge “roof.”  

Right Tower (total of 7 blocks, stacked in 5 layers):  
1) Bottom layer: a green rectangular block.  
2) Above it: one upright orange cylinder.  
3) Next: a flat yellow rectangular block, forming the lower “bar” of a square frame.  
4) Two vertical green rectangular blocks on that yellow bar (left and right sides), with an orange triangular wedge placed between them.  
5) Finally, another flat yellow block bridging across the two green uprights, completing a large square “window” around the wedge.  

Required Blocks from the Dictionary
------------------------------------
• For the Left Tower (7 blocks):  
  – 3× Index 10 (yellow flat rectangular block)  
  – 1× Index 3  (red block with a circular hole)  
  – 2× Index 11 (orange cylinder, upright)  
  – 1× Index 16 (orange triangular wedge)  

• For the Right Tower (7 blocks):  
  – 1× Index 4  (green rectangular block, horizontally oriented)  
  – 1× Index 11 (orange cylinder, upright)  
  – 2× Index 6  (green rectangular block, vertically oriented)  
  – 2× Index 10 (yellow flat rectangular block)  
  – 1× Index 16 (orange triangular wedge)  

Assembly Order
---------------
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 10     (Left tower bottom)  
  Step2: Move block with index 3      (Red circular‐hole block)  
  Step3: Move block with index 10     (Mid‐level yellow platform)  
  Step4: Move block with index 11     (First orange cylinder)  
  Step5: Move block with index 11     (Second orange cylinder)  
  Step6: Move block with index 10     (Top yellow plank)  
  Step7: Move block with index 16     (Orange wedge roof)  

  Step8:  Move block with index 4     (Right tower green base)  
  Step9:  Move block with index 11    (Orange cylinder on base)  
  Step10: Move block with index 10    (Lower yellow bar of “window”)  
  Step11: Move block with index 6     (Left green upright)  
  Step12: Move block with index 6     (Right green upright)  
  Step13: Move block with index 16    (Orange wedge in center)  
  Step14: Move block with index 10    (Top yellow bar of “window”)  
}
